  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The development by reason of the provision of a poor standard of accomodation for future occupants of the HMO would be directly contarty to LP22 (Houses in Multiple Occupation) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "The development, in absence of details in connection with rent levels, management arrangements and length of tenancy agreements fails to demonstrate that the development is acceptable in land use terms. As such, the proposal is contrary to policy LP22 (Houses in Multiple Occupation (HMO)) of the Hackney Local Development Plan (2020).",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of Hackney Local Development Plan (2020).&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of no provision of cycle parking would fail to promote sustainable modes of transport. As such the proposed development is contrary to policies T5 (Cycling) of the London Plan 2021, policies LP42 (Walking and Cycling) and LP43 (Transport and Development) of the Local Plan 2033(2020) and the guidance contained within Hackney Transport Strategy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "The development, by reason of the loss of&amp;nbsp; existing housing suitable for family occupation, would result in the undersupply of family sized dwellings in the borough, to the detriments of the boroughs identified housing need. As such, the development is contrary to policies LP12 (Meeting Housing Needs and Locations for New Homes), LP22 (Houses in Multiple Occupation (HMO)) of Hackney’s Local Development Plan (2020) and policy H8 (Loss of Existing Housing and Estate Redevelopment) of the London Plan (2021)."
  ],
